.el .ds Aq '
.TH manta-delete 1  "delete " 
.SH NAME
manta\-delete \- Remove nodes, groups, images, configurations, sessions, boot/kernel parameters, or Redfish endpoints
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmanta delete\fR [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fIsubcommands\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Remove nodes, groups, images, configurations, sessions, boot/kernel parameters, or Redfish endpoints
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
manta\-delete\-group(1)
Delete a node group
.TP
manta\-delete\-node(1)
Remove a node from the hardware state manager
.TP
manta\-delete\-nodes(1)
Remove nodes from a group
.TP
manta\-delete\-kernel\-parameters(1)
Remove kernel parameters from nodes (parameter values are ignored — match is by name)
.TP
manta\-delete\-boot\-parameters(1)
Delete boot parameters for nodes
.TP
manta\-delete\-configurations(1)
Delete configurations and all associated data
.TP
manta\-delete\-session(1)
Delete a configuration session
.TP
manta\-delete\-images(1)
[experimental] Delete IMS images by ID (refuses to delete images currently booting a node)
.TP
manta\-delete\-hardware(1)
[experimental] Remove hardware components from a group
.TP
manta\-delete\-redfish\-endpoints(1)
Delete a Redfish endpoint
